= step 'traditional-vs-single-page', x: 6000 do
  %div.row
    %div.span5
      %h4 Traditional
      %ul
        %li HTML rendered on server.
        %li Each link loads an entirely new page.
        %li Simple page interactions.
        %li Higher server load.
        %li Increased caching complexity.
        %li Server is difficult to consume by non-html clients.
    %div.span5
      %h4 Single Page
      %ul
        %li HTML rendered in browser.
        %li Pages and content are built dynamically.
        %li Rich user experience.
        %li Simpler caching strategies
        %li Reduced server load.
        %li May use the same server to build other client applications.

